item.title: LM2536 HOLDER V2
item.description: This is a robust LM2596 module casing. Module and cover are fixed with common self-tapping screw 3x10mm you can find them in any store. Cables are locked by cover and common zip ties. This casing allow module to be securely wall mounted with four 4mm holes or double sided tape in the flat back. Print can be done with any resolution and use two small support for zip ties holes. It's really easy to remove.

item.title: Work Rezax Hex Tool 17"/18"
item.description:
Hi,

This is a quick hex tool I drew up in order to screw down properly the hex cap on work rezax rims as they have a tendency to come loose.
There's a small pry bar on the end to help lift up the waffle upon removal.

Infill should be at least 20% but no more than 40% (although it's up to you), would much rather the tool break than the threads on the hex strip.

This works on both 17'' and 18'' hex caps both tall and short.

Designed to be printed without supports.

Let me know if there's anything that needs to be edited.
Step files available for editing.

Thanks.
item.author: ICEBLOCK

item.title: Proxxon Micromot 12V tools socket / plug for panel mount
item.description:
This is a plug shell for Proxxon Micromot series of tools, which operate on 12V power.

It has 2 halves which bolt together (4mm bolt fits in the hole), and for contacts, it uses butt connectors (without the plastic sleeve), similiar to https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3437152

The butt connectors should be solid all the way around (so not have a split to help crush them), and be a tight fit around the tools plugs poles.

I used butt connectors called "VT STV-B Butt connector, 1.5 - 2.5 mm²", bough from here: https://www.reichelt.com/de/en/butt-connector-1-5-2-5-mm-blue-vt-stv-b-p231400.html, however, there must be similiar connectors available elsewhere too, you might want to test others before ordering those if you find the shipping expensive.

The plug is designed to slide into a slot in a panel. I have however included the .blend file as well if you want to edit this more easily.
item.author: Okxa

item.title: Hotend adapter Creality CR6 SE to CR 10 / ENDER 3
item.description:
Due to the low availability of spare parts for CR6 i decided to make myself an adapter for hotend that i can mount hotend from creality cr 10. I have never done such things so process was very long and the result is awful, but it works! Works really well, my printer is making much better prints than before.

Dont do supports inside screw holes!

There are holes to mount a fan, but i found it works better when i mount fan on the hotend case.

I printed it using standard PLA, with ABS, adapter for sure will last much longer :)

Fell free to improve this model, he really needs this!

I used 0.4mm nozzle, i dont know if holes for screws dont gonna be to big with smaller nozzles.

item.title: Multi-function woodworking tool
item.description:
A multi-function woodworking tool (for left and right handed)

  • scribing ruler
  • 22.5, 45, 67.5 and 90 degree square
  • saw guide for cutting at 22.5, 45, 67.5 and 90 degrees

The saw guide is particularly suitable for Japanese saws (kataba style for example).

There are four parts to print

1 The main body with the ruler (support needed under the thread)
The thread can be reinforced with a M5 screw of at least 35 mm if necessary. You can also increase infill percent in the thread.

2 The ruler which can be glued under the body (position according to left/right hand) without support

3 The nut without support

4 The saw guide with a support at the hole.
There are two saw guides provided.
One for blades under 50 mm and one for blades under 70 mm. Choose according to your saw.

item.title: Zonestar P802Q series z-bottom fix bracket
item.description: Zonestar P802Q series is a 3d printer that is one of "clones" of Prusa i3 with stainless frame. The stainless bracket of z-axes of those printers' fixes only the stepper motors but the z linear shafts are in holes drilled on the brackets. The diameter of the hole is greater than the shaft about 0.5mm so the shaft moves in all directions. This parts is a remix of "z-axis-bottom.stl" on https://www.prusaprinters.org/prints/57217-i3-mk3s-printable-parts/files .
